trend_summary: Between the earliest and latest scenes the corridor shows moderate infill: warehouses enlarge along the southern river, new rooftops appear in northern neighbourhoods, and a highway interchange is rebuilt. Simultaneously vegetation spreads on slopes and a linear greenway forms by the river. Overall land-use shifts from mixed industrial/residential toward a greener, moderately built suburban fabric.
notable_changes: Expansion and consolidation of warehouse blocks in the southern industrial zone.
Reconfiguration and widening of the main highway interchange at the southern tip.
Continuous tree-canopy gain on hillsides and within neighbourhood streets.
Addition of a riverside greenway or park strip where rail or vacant land existed.
Scattered residential infill and several new light-colored roofs in the northern sector.
